# Amanak testing

## Tooling

- **Unit / integration**: `vitest` + React Testing Library (`happy-dom`). Setup: `vitest.setup.ts` imports `@testing-library/jest-dom/vitest`.
- **E2E**: Playwright (`e2e/smoke.spec.ts`). Default `webServer` runs `pnpm dev --port 3000` (reuse existing server locally when not in CI).

## Commands

```bash
pnpm test        # vitest run
pnpm test:watch  # vitest dev
pnpm exec playwright install   # once per machine (Firefox/Chromium/WebKit)
pnpm test:e2e    # playwright test (defaults to Firefox; PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSER=chromium to override)
```

## Per-feature expectations

| Feature | Unit / RTL | E2E |
|--------|------------|-----|
| Inquiry validation (`inquiryFormSchema`) | Required | Part of inquiry submit flow |
| Locale routing + switcher | Optional focused test | `en` → `ar` link updates URL |
| Mobile drawer | Sheet behavior RTL side | Open menu → navigate to inquiry |
| Landing composition | Optional | Landing heading visible on `/ar` |
| Mock submit | — | Success copy after POST client journey |

## Playwright conventions

- Prefer **`data-testid`** only where accessibility labels are ambiguous across locales (`nav-menu-trigger`, `inquiry-submit`).
- Use **`getByRole` + accessible names** in the user’s language when stable (Arabic labels on `/ar` inquiry form).

## Do / Don’t

- **Do** add a unit test when introducing non-trivial Zod/schema logic or pricing-like pure functions (future).
- **Do** extend smoke e2e when adding a new critical journey (e.g. `/estimate` wizard later).
- **Don’t** rely on production APIs in Playwright for this prototype; keep mocks deterministic.
